commit.message:
Make statement cache recycle bin be per connection

Fixes #505

New hash algorithm in previous commit.

Wasted time dedicated to PyMem_Free being a macro that
evaluates its arguments multiple times.
use $(MAKE) not make for hygiene
Bump to python 3.12 for debug/valgrind builds
Cast to avoid compiler warning

Stop using _Py_HashBytes

It was never a public API, although handy.

Running speed test showed a 0.8% to 2.2% improvement so this
makes APSW faster too.

Addresses part of #511

Implements most of #505

Duplicate the prototype of _PyErr_ChainExceptions1 for Py 3.13

See https://github.com/python/cpython/issues/116809

Refs https://github.com/rogerbinns/apsw/issues/511
Link to method that exposes sqlite3_serialize
megatest tweaks
Update generated files
sqlite3_serialize on empty db changes
SQLite release bump

Use Iterable instead of Sequence type annotation

Fixes #508
SQLite release bump

Make it clear that the future annotations import is mandatory

Refs #507

Add in python3-venv

Quite why debian/ubuntu feel the need to exclude it I
don't know
Use podman for megatest
Sync for download/upload v4 changes

Fix upload-artifact@v4 changes

Error message was

[error]Failed to CreateArtifact: Received non-retryable error: Failed request: (409) Conflict: an artifact with this name already exists on the workflow run

Following instructions at
https://github.com/actions/upload-artifact/issues/478#issuecomment-1885470013
